       <article class="post-141 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-machines category-macro category-photography" id="post-141">
        <header class="entry-header">
         <h1 class="entry-title">
          Watch Detail
         </h1>
         <div class="entry-meta">
          <span class="meta-prep meta-prep-author">
           Posted
          </span>
          <a href="http://peterholdmann.com/2014/06/15/watch-detail/" rel="bookmark">
           <time class="entry-date" datetime="2014-06-15T20:27:14+00:00" pubdate="">
            June 15, 2014
           </time>
          </a>
          <span class="meta-sep">
           by
          </span>
          <span class="author vcard">
           <a class="url fn n" href="http://peterholdmann.com/author/peter/" title="View all posts by Peter">
            Peter
           </a>
          </span>
         </div>
         <!-- .entry-meta -->
        </header>
        <!-- .entry-header -->
        <div class="entry-content">
         <p>
          <a href="http://peterholdmann.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Watch-DSC_0293.jpg">
           <img alt="Watch-DSC_0293" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-140" height="997" src="http://peterholdmann.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Watch-DSC_0293.jpg" width="1500"/>
          </a>
         </p>
         <p>
          Detail of the back of my Seiko 5 automatic watch.
         </p>
         <p>
          For those unfamiliar with them, the
          <a href="http://www.amazon.com/s/?_encoding=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;field-keywords=Seiko%205%20watch&amp;linkCode=ur2&amp;tag=phcontent-20&amp;url=search-alias%3Daps" target="_blank">
           Seiko 5 series
          </a>
          is a great introductory line of automatic (self-winding) watches. They run in the $50-100+ range, and keep pretty reasonable time. They also have an exhibition back, so you can see the clockwork inside.
         </p>
         <p>
          D100,
          <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00005LE77/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B00005LE77&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=phcontent-20" target="_blank" title="Affiliate Link, I may be recompenced for purchases">
           60mm f2.8D Micro-Nikkor
          </a>
          , f16 at 1/60, ISO 200 with a cheap flash bounced off a Westocott reflector for lighting.
         </p>
         <p>
          Like what you see?
          <a href="http://twitter.com/peterholdmann" target="_blank">
           Follow me on Twitter
          </a>
          for updates.
         </p>
